<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-31-0404 </DOCNO><TEXT>A patient diagnosed as having ankylosing spondylitis 6 months later developedsymptoms resembling lung tuberculosis, although no bacterial evidencecould be obtained to support that diagnosis. Because a large solitarycavity of the left upper lobe was observed, a thoracotomy was performedwhich yielded histological evidence supporting a diagnosis of lung fibrosis.The etiology, clinical appearance and therapy of the syndrom, first describedin 1949 by Hamilton, is discussed.</TEXT></DOC>